  <?dbhtml dir="menuBarComponent"?>
  <title>Concrete toolkit menu bar component</title>
  <para>
  	<itemizedlist>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				A <emphasis>menu bar</emphasis> is the component typically found at the top of an application window.
   			</para>
  		</listitem>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				It typically contains menus such as <emphasis>"File", "Edit", "Help", etc.</emphasis>.
  			</para>
  		</listitem>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				Because the forward slash (/) is a special symbol for menus, if you want to use a slash as part
  				of your parameter value, you have to mask it.
  			</para>
  		</listitem>
  		<listitem>
  			<para>
  				Menu bars do not need to be mapped in the Object Mapping Mode as they are automatically found during
  				test execution.
  			</para>
  		</listitem>
  	</itemizedlist>
  </para>
  <para role="warning">
    Actions on menus are not supported in the HTML toolkit.
  </para>
